<subSubSection id="B8CC65052C01FFBDFD01A09F96116509" pageId="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="F069368E2C01FFBDFD01A09F96116509" blockId="4.[734,1329,1911,2338]" pageId="4">
<taxonomicName id="37D64D0D2C01FFBDFD01A09F91236BCC" authorityName="Coues" authorityYear="1875" box="[737,815,1990,2023]" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Zapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Zapus</taxonomicName>
rinkeri from Kansas is the oldest known North American 
<taxonomicName id="37D64D0D2C01FFBDFBA3A0B7969D6424" authorityName="Coues" authorityYear="1875" box="[1091,1169,2030,2063]" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Zapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Zapus</taxonomicName>
and forms a successive series with Z. burti and Z. hudsonius. 
<taxonomicName id="37D64D0D2C01FFBDFCACAF6591966476" authorityName="Coues" authorityYear="1875" box="[844,922,2108,2141]" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Zapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Zapus</taxonomicName>
sandersi is from the Great Plains, and Z. burt: is from Kansas. 
<taxonomicName id="37D64D0D2C01FFBDFB02AF35973C64AE" authorityName="Coues" authorityYear="1875" box="[1250,1328,2156,2181]" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Zapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Zapus</taxonomicName>
burti may have been ancestral to 
<taxonomicName id="37D64D0D2C01FFBDFB25AFD2912C64FF" authorityName="Rhoads" authorityYear="1895" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Zapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="trinotatus">Z. trinotatus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="37D64D0D2C01FFBDFC92AFEA960C64FF" authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1893" box="[882,1024,2227,2260]" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Zapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="princeps">Z. princeps</taxonomicName>
, and both may have arisen from the 
<taxonomicName id="37D64D0D2C01FFBDFC30AF83967764D0" baseAuthorityName="Zimmermann" baseAuthorityYear="1780" box="[976,1147,2266,2299]" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Zapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hudsonius">Z. hudsonius</taxonomicName>
line. Eleven subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
